The paper focuses on signal processing techniques for deconvolving mixed tissues/cell types, which is a problem commonly encountered in bioinformatics and computational biology. The paper discusses various models, methods, and assumptions underlying deconvolution techniques, which are typically used in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.BIO (Computational Biology).
